						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Āditya II, Year 4 = c. 968-9 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The king is mentioned as Parakesarivarman, ‘who took the head of Vīra-Pāṇḍya’. Gift of a lamp to the temple of Aṟṟuttaḷi-Mahādēvar at Tirumuḍiyūr in Tirumunaippāḍi. The donor was Chivageṅga-palavaraiyan of Chemaṇaṅgūr on the south bank.</p>						

